e old milwaukee brewers minor league team and the chicago cubs he became a braves fan when the national league franchise moved to milwaukee from boston in  he subsequently became the teams largest public stockholder before selling his stock in  when the team moved to atlanta upon learning of the braves intended move to atlanta selig founded teams inc an organization dedicated to returning major league baseball to milwaukee the group which later changed its name to the brewers arranged for several chicago white sox games to be played in milwaukee in  after failing to purchase the white sox in  seligs efforts were finally rewarded on april   when a seattle bankruptcy court awarded the seattle pilots franchise to selig and his investors the brewers appeared in the  world series losing to the st louis cardinals in seven games the club won seven organization of the year awards during seligs tenure as club president including the topps organization of the year award in    and  in addition the brewers won an unprecedented threestraight baseball america awards from  seligs active role in baseball in the milwaukee community and throughout the nation has resulted in his receiving many awards during his career including selected as the executive of the year by sportsbusiness journalsportsbusiness daily on december   honored with the  diversity leadership award at the diversity and women leadership summit and gala on november   recipient of the judge emil fuchs award by the boston chapter of the baseball writers association of america for long and meritorious service to baseball on january   awarded the recognition of goodness award by the prestigious jewish foundation for the righteous an organization that provides financial support to aging nonjews who risked their lives to save others during the holocaust for his extensive charitable efforts on december   in new york city recipient of the urban hero award for his support of urban youth initiatives at the eighth annual urban heroes award benefit on june   recipient of the baseball assistance teams big batfrank slocum award given january   to honor his contributions and support of bat inducted into the wisconsin athletic hall of fame november   sports torch of learning award presented to outstanding leaders in the field of sports from the american friends of hebrew university july   created the allan h and suzanne l selig merit scholarship fund to the rothberg international school at the hebrew university of jerusalem recipient of the human relations award from the national conference for community and justice june   recipient of the sports leadership award from greater ny chapter of the march of dimes december   master of the game award from marquette univ sports law institute september   inducted into wisconsin business hall of fame may   received the good scout award from boy scouts of america december   the herbert hoover humanitarian award received november   from the boys and girls clubs of america for outstanding service to benefit americas youth the distinguished service award from the us sports academy in  named wisconsins top sports personality of the past  years an award by the milwaukee pen  mike club february  recipient of the world of difference award from the antidefamation league february  received the ellis island medal of honor awarded to outstanding citizens of the united states who have contributed to our national identity while preserving the distinct values and heritage of their ancestors may   received the distinguished citizen award from the potawatomi council of the boy scouts of america december  recipient of the august a busch jr award presented by major league baseball ownership september  the award given for long and meritorious service to baseball is the equivalent for offfield personnel to the players most valuable player award received the baird award for management excellence april  the baird award is given annually to a wisconsin corporation that co