beyond a few famous players such as greenberg rosen koufax holtzman green ausmus youkilis braun and kinsler in fact that presence extends to the baseball commissioner bud selig labor leaders marvin miller and don fehr owners jerry reinsdorf and stuart sternberg officials theo epstein and mark shapiro sportswriters murray chass ross newhan ira berkow and roger kahn and even famous jewish baseball fans like alan dershowitz and barney frank the life stories of these and many others on and off the field have been compiled from nearly fifty indepth interviews and arranged by decade in this edifying and entertaining work of oral and cultural history in american jews and americas game each person talks about growing up jewish and dealing with jewish identity assimilation intermarriage future viability religious observance antisemitism and israel each tells about being in the midst of the colorful pantheon of players who over the past seventyfive years or more have made baseball what it is their stories tell as no previous book has the history of the largerthanlife role of jews in americas pastimeshow more product details format hardback   pages dimensions  x  x mm  g publication date  apr  publisher university of nebraska press publication citycountry lincoln united states language english illustrations note  photographs  drawings isbn  isbn  people who bought this also bought off the baseball talmud howard megdal  apr  hardback us  us save us add to basket off hank greenberg mark kurlansky  mar  hardback us  us save us add to basket jewish major leaguers in their own words peter ephross  mar  paperback us add to basket jews and baseball burton a boxerman  dec  hardback us add to basket off catcher was a spy nicholas dawidoff  dec  paperback us  us save us add to basket off out of left field rebecca t alpert  jun  hardback us  us save us add to basket off jewish jocks franklin foer  oct  paperback us  us save us add to basket women of valor sheila segal  oct  paperback us 