g that i had ever been to and i knew then that if this sport was to go on to the heights that i believed it could it needed revenue sharing it needed other rules to change – allan h bud selig major league baseball   biography allan h bud selig episode  winning the game the roughandtumble business of sports featured guest allan h bud selig commissioner major league baseball mr seligs video clip allan h bud selig was elected the ninth commissioner of baseball on july   by a unanimous vote of the  major league baseball club owners selig was born on july   in milwaukee and received a bachelors degree in american history and political science from the university of wisconsin – madison in  after serving two years in the armed forces selig returned to milwaukee and began working in the automobile business with his father selig maintains a tie to that industry as president of the selig executive lease company a lifelong baseball fan selig while growing up followed the old milwaukee brewers minor league team and the chicago cubs he became a braves fan when the national league franchise moved to milwaukee from boston in  he subsequently became the teams largest public stockholder before selling his stock in  when the team moved to atlanta upon learning of the braves intended move to atlanta selig founded teams inc an organization dedicated to returning major league baseball to milwaukee the group which later changed its name to the brewers arranged for several chicago white sox games to be played in milwaukee in  after failing to purchase the white sox in  seligs efforts were finally rewarded on april   when a seattle bankruptcy court awarded the seattle pilots franchise to selig and his investors the brewers appeared in the  world series losing to the st louis cardinals in seven games the club won seven organization of the year awards during seligs tenure as club president including the topps organization of the year award in    and  in addition the brewers won an unprecedented threestraight baseball america awards from  seligs active role in baseball in the milwaukee community and throughout the nation has resulted in his receiving many awards during his career including recipient of the judge emil fuchs award by the boston chapter of the baseball writers association of america for long and meritorious service to baseball on january   awarded the recognition of goodness award by the prestigious jewish foundation for the righteous an organization that provides financial support to aging nonjews who risked their lives to save others during the holocaust for his extensive charitable efforts on december   in new york city recipient of the urban hero award for his support of urban youth initiatives at the eighth annual urban heroes award benefit on june   recipient of the baseball assistance teams big batfrank slocum award given january   to honor his contributions and support of bat inducted into the wisconsin athletic hall of fame november   sports torch of learning award presented to outstanding leaders in the field of sports from the american friends of hebrew university july   created the allan h and suzanne l selig merit scholarship fund to the rothberg international school at the hebrew university of jerusalem recipient of the human relations award from the national conference for community and justice june   recipient of the sports leadership award from greater ny chapter of the march of dimes december   master of the game award from marquette univ sports law institute september   inducted into wisconsin business hall of fame may   received the good scout award from boy scouts of america december   the herbert hoover humanitarian award received november   from the boys and girls clubs of america for outstanding service to benefit americas youth the distinguished service award from the us sports academy in  named  wisconsins top sports personality of the past  years an award by the milwaukee pen  mike club february  recipient of the world of difference award from the antidefamation league february  received the ellis island medal of honor awarded to outstanding citizens of the united states who have contributed to our national identity while preserving the distinct values and heritage of their ancestors may   received the distinguished citizen award from the potawatomi council of the boy scouts of america december  recipient of the august a busch jr award presented by major league baseball ownership september  the award given for long and meritorious service to baseball is the equivalent for offfield personnel to the players most valuable player award received the baird award for management excellence april  the baird award is given annually to a wisconsin corporation that consistently demonstrates superior financial achievement and community involvement named the united states olympic committee sportsman of the year award for his contributions to baseball and to youth in milwaukee may  received the international bnai brith sportsman of the year award for his distinguished contributions to the world of sports february  named major league executive of the year by united press international  selig is a member of the board of directors of the green bay packers inc marcus corporation and the oildri corporation of america he is also on the board of visitors for the department of political science and the la follette school of public affairs at the university of wisconsin selig is a member of the greater milwaukee committee the boys and girls clubs board of trustees is a founder of athletes for youth and was instrumental in establishing the child abuse prevention cap fund bud and his wife sue are very active in the milwaukee community and were corecipients of the  humanitarian award from the st francis childrens center they also lend their support and time to the milwaukee art museum in july of  the allan h and suzanne l selig merit scholarship fund was established at the rothberg international school at the hebrew university of jerusalem selig who was active in the governance of major league baseball during his tenure as president of the milwaukee brewers was a member of the major league executive council when commissioner fay vincent resigned on september   in accordance with the major league agreement which grants the executive council the authority to rule baseball in the absence of a commissioner selig became the central figure in baseballs power structure on september   when his fellow owners named him chairman of the major league executive council selig served a dual role as president of the milwaukee brewers baseball club and chairman of the executive council until his appointment as commissioner on july   at that time his financial interest in the club was placed in trust and he relinquished involvement in all matters dealing with the operation of the brewers in january  the brewers were sold to mark attanasio thus ending seligs year relationship with the club as chairman of the executive council and then as commissioner seligs ability to rule by consensus brought about numerous dramatic changes to baseball including unbalanced schedule interleague play significant revenue sharing among clubs threedivision formats in the american and national leagues an extra tier of playoffs and the wild card first phase of realignment consolidation of the administrative functions of the american and national leagues into the commissioners office the restoration of the rulebook strike zone award the home field advantage in the world series to the team that represents the league that won the allstar game but most important on august   selig engineered an historic labor agreement with the major league baseball players association that avoided a work stoppage and provided significant economic concessions to the clubs those concessions have brought on greater competitive balance among the clubs for the first time in  years the clubs and the players association were able to reach a labor agreement without either a strike or a lockout and on january   major league baseball and the major league baseball players association announced an historic agreement to expand its drugtesting program to include random yearround testing immediate discipline and broader list of banned substances the new program which is as strong as any in professional sports brought to an end a longterm effort by selig to try to rid the game of illegal steroids and performance enhancing substances under his leadership as executive council chairman and commissioner new stadiums have opened in arizona atlanta cincinnati cleveland colorado detroit houston milwaukee pittsburgh philadelphia san diego san francisco seattle and texas another is scheduled to open in  in st louis despite presiding over the game during a troubled period that included a day player strike in  and  selig is in the process of guiding the game through a significant renaissance major league baseball set an alltime attendance record in  as  fans attended games at the  ballparks that figure broke the previous record set in  and was an  percent improvement over the  season total of  bud and his wife sue have three daughters and five granddaughters exclusively underwritten by   produced by   in association with       window to the world communications inc last updated june   privacy policy